{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885375202,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04514b001cuUE2NXfhPg2N4","messageID":"msg_d7b044317001YJJpG6eSMhkMeN","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ea0099ac1c2a4277a15e883f5d3b5d23","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-029\n5: - **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n6: - **Module**: sdk-python\n7: - **Language**: Python\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n17: The system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n20: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n21: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n22: - **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n25: - **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n26: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n27: - **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n30: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n31: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n32: - **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n35: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n36: - **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n37: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\n40: The system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n43: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n44: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n45: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n48: - **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n49: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n50: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n53: - **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n54: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n55: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\n58: The system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Delete session success\n61: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n62: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n63: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n66: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n67: - **WHEN** the response is received\n68: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n71: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n72: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n73: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\n76: The system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n79: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n80: - **WHEN** requests are made\n81: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n84: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n85: - **WHEN** requests are made\n86: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n89: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n90: - **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n91: - **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n94: The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n97: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n98: - **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n99: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n102: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n103: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n104: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n105: \n106: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\n107: The system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Request includes session header\n110: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n111: - **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n112: - **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n115: - **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n116: - **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n117: - **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n120: - **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n121: - **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n122: - **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\n125: The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n128: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n129: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n130: - **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n133: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n134: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n135: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n136: \n137: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\n138: The system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n141: - **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n142: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n143: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n146: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n147: - **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n148: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n151: - **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n152: - **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n153: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: List files in directory\n156: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n157: - **WHEN** the request completes\n158: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n161: The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n164: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n165: - **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n166: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\n169: The system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n172: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n173: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n174: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n177: - **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n178: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n179: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\n182: The system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n185: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n186: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n187: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n190: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n191: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n192: - **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n195: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n196: - **WHEN** the method executes\n197: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\n200: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n203: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n204: - **WHEN** the session is created\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n208: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n209: - **WHEN** the session is created\n210: - **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n213: - **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n214: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n215: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\n218: The system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n221: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n222: - **WHEN** the block exits\n223: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n226: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n227: - **WHEN** the block exits\n228: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n231: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n232: - **WHEN** the block exits\n233: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n234: \n235: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\n236: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n239: - **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n240: - **WHEN** the error is raised\n241: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n244: - **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n245: - **WHEN** the error is raised\n246: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n247: \n248: ### Requirement: Token file reading utility\n249: The system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Read existing token file\n252: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n253: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n254: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n257: - **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n258: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n260: \n261: ### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\n262: The system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n265: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n266: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n270: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n271: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n273: \n274: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n275: \n276: 1. ✅ ControlPlaneClient resolves environment variables for base_url and auth_token\n277: 2. ✅ ControlPlaneClient creates sessions via POST with proper headers and JSON body\n278: 3. ✅ ControlPlaneClient deletes sessions via DELETE with 404 tolerance\n279: 4. ✅ ControlPlaneClient uses configurable timeouts and connection pooling\n280: 5. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name\n281: 6. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient injects x-agentcube-session-id header in all requests\n282: 7. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands with timeout buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n283: 8. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient supports write, upload, download, and list file operations\n284: 9. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name\n285: 10. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session ID via GET request\n286: 11. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invokes workloads via POST with JSON payload\n287: 12. ✅ HTTP session management uses requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n288: 13. ✅ Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n289: 14. ✅ Exception hierarchy defines AgentCubeError, SessionError, and DataPlaneError\n290: 15. ✅ Token file reading utility reads Kubernetes service account tokens\n291: 16. ✅ Logger configuration utility provides consistent logger setup\n292: \n293: ## Dependencies\n294: \n295: - `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n296: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n297: - `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n298: - Python >=3.10\n299: \n300: ## References\n301: \n302: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n303: - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n304: - AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n(End of file - total 304 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885375164,"end":1775885375200}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885375206,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b045357001hwKwBAMXs5Oulh","messageID":"msg_d7b044317001YJJpG6eSMhkMeN","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-74ae56fc7a2a40d7b0b106a5de776d85","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775885375166,"end":1775885375204}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885375208,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04556d0016XkMiCUn5ylywC","messageID":"msg_d7b044317001YJJpG6eSMhkMeN","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-620feb62059643a180736b59468f3f6c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key s