{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885395842,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b049ee4001Nh6G86U4z6rlVy","messageID":"msg_d7b04951b0012SKFi65HAVv63q","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4c50e33b21c148488c53924f1a751af0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: This document describes the delta specification for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: Define the changes required to implement 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation.\n8: \n9: ## Detailed Specification\n10: \n11: TBD - Will be populated during specification phase.\n\n(End of file - total 11 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 Delta Specification\n\nThis document describes the delta specification for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the changes required to implement 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation.\n\n## Detailed Specification\n\nTBD - Will be populated during specification phase.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885395829,"end":1775885395841}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885395844,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04a1a9001W0DVcnFGn4S26H","messageID":"msg_d7b04951b0012SKFi65HAVv63q","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4c6f03872fd14390b80e3f091ed0be7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 Specification\n2: \n3: This document contains the full specification for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: Complete specification for implementing 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation in the AgentCube project.\n8: \n9: ## Detailed Specification\n10: \n11: TBD - Will be populated during specification phase.\n\n(End of file - total 11 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 Specification\n\nThis document contains the full specification for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n\n## Overview\n\nComplete specification for implementing 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation in the AgentCube project.\n\n## Detailed Specification\n\nTBD - Will be populated during specification phase.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md","time":{"start":1775885395832,"end":1775885395843}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885395895,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04a472001aKsh8ZsgkNG0nO","messageID":"msg_d7b04951b0012SKFi65HAVv63q","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-66fdc3b0ef4e4f5b809fd6b9301a8b4f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 Design\n2: \n3: This document contains the design decisions and architecture for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n4: \n5: ## Architecture Overview\n6: \n7: TBD - Will be populated during design phase.\n8: \n9: ## Design Decisions\n10: \n11: TBD - Will be populated during design phase.\n\n(End of file - total 11 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 Design\n\nThis document contains the design decisions and architecture for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows).\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nTBD - Will be populated during design phase.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\nTBD - Will be populated during design phase.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/design.md","time":{"start":1775885395875,"end":1775885395893}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885395899,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04a755001jrrhpxzKh7goXR","messageID":"msg_d7b04951b0012SKFi65HAVv63q","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a9c040d0739c4c81aedb1a7f90f47d09","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: 为 AgentCube 项目实现 12 个 GitHub Actions 工作流，提供完整的 CI/CD 自动化能力。这些工作流将覆盖构建、测试、代码质量检查、端到端测试、Python SDK 验证、镜像发布等关键流程，确保代码质量和持续交付的可靠性。\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 实现完整的 CI/CD 自动化体系，达到以下目标：\n10: \n11: - **自动化验证** - 对 Pull Request 自动执行构建、Lint、测试、代码生成漂移检查\n12: - **质量保证** - 多层次的代码质量检查（Go Lint、Python Lint、Spelling、Copyright）\n13: - **测试覆盖** - 单元测试、集成测试、端到端测试、覆盖率报告\n14: - **持续交付** - 自动构建和推送多架构容器镜像到 GHCR\n15: - **开发体验** - 简化开发流程，快速反馈代码问题\n16: - **多语言支持** - 同时支持 Go 和 Python 项目的工作流\n17: - **Kubernetes 集成** - 在 Kind 上运行 E2E 测试\n18: - **安全合规** - 工作流审批机制保护首次贡献者\n19: \n20: ## Module\n21: \n22: `.github` - GitHub Actions 工作流目录\n23: \n24: ## Language\n25: \n26: YAML (GitHub Actions workflow syntax)\n27: \n28: ## Size\n29: \n30: L\n31: \n32: ## Scope\n33: \n34: ### In Scope\n35: \n36: #### 1. CI 工作流 (ci.yml)\n37: - **触发条件**: Pull Request 到 `main` 或 `release-*` 分支\n38: - **主要任务**:\n39:   - Docker Buildx 设置\n40:   - 构建 Workload Manager Docker 镜像\n41:   - 验证 docker/buildx 版本\n42:   - 执行 `make docker-build`\n43: \n44: #### 2. Lint 工作流 (lint.yml)\n45: - **触发条件**: Pull Request 到 `main` 或 `release-*` 分支\n46: - **路径过滤**: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n47: - **主要任务**:\n48:   - 设置 Go 1.24 环境\n49:   - 执行 `make lint` (golangci-lint)\n50: \n51: #### 3. 代码生成检查工作流 (codegen-check.yml)\n52: - **触发条件**: Pull Request\n53: - **路径过滤**: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n54: - **主要任务**:\n55:   - 设置 Go 1.24.4 环境\n56:   - 执行 `make gen-check`\n57:   - 验证生成产物无漂移\n58: \n59: #### 4. 测试覆盖率工作流 (test-coverage.yml)\n60: - **触发条件**: Pull Request 和 merge group\n61: - **主要任务**:\n62:   - 设置 Go 1.24 环境\n63:   - 运行竞态检测和覆盖率测试\n64:   - 执行 `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n65:   - 上传 coverage.out 工件\n66:   - 可选：上传到 Codecov\n67: \n68: #### 5. E2E 测试工作流 (e2e.yml)\n69: - **触发条件**: Pull Request 到 `main` 或 `release-*` 分支\n70: - **主要任务**:\n71:   - 设置 Go 1.23 环境\n72:   - 安装 Kind v0.30.0\n73:   - 设置 `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n74:   - 执行 `make e2e`\n75:   - 失败时上传 e2e-logs 工件\n76:   - 始终执行 `make e2e-clean`\n77: \n78: #### 6. Python SDK 测试工作流 (python-sdk-test.yml)\n79: - **触发条件**: Pull Request\n80: - **路径过滤**: `sdk-python/**`\n81: - **主要任务**:\n82:   - 设置 Python 3.12 环境\n83:   - 切换到 `sdk-python/` 目录\n84:   - 安装 pytest 和 SDK (`pip install -e .`)\n85:   - 运行 `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n86: \n87: #### 7. Python Lint 工作流 (python-lint.yml)\n88: - **触发条件**: Pull Request\n89: - **路径过滤**: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, 工作流文件\n90: - **主要任务**:\n91:   - 设置 Python 3.10 环境\n92:   - 安装 ruff\n93:   - 执行 `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n94: \n95: #### 8. 拼写检查工作流 (spelling.yml)\n96: - **触发条件**: Pull Request 到 `main` 或 `release-*` 分支\n97: - **主要任务**:\n98:   - 安装 codespell\n99:   - 备份/移动 `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` (根目录和嵌套)\n100:   - 执行 codespell 检查（带文件名检查、跳过规则、忽略单词列表）\n101:   - 恢复备份文件\n102:   - 忽略单词列表: `fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn`\n103: \n104: #### 9. Copyright 检查工作流 (copyright.yml)\n105: - **触发条件**: Pull Request\n106: - **路径过滤**: 除 `.md`, `.svg`, `.png`, `docs/`, `.github/` 外的所有路径\n107: - **主要任务**:\n108:   - 安装 moreutils (sponge)\n109:   - 执行 `make gen-copyright`\n110:   - 验证 `git diff --exit-code` 无变更\n111: \n112: #### 10. 发布工作流 (release.yml)\n113: - **触发条件**: Push 到 `main` 分支或 semantic version tags\n114: - **主要任务**:\n115:   - 确定 TAG（tag 时使用 `github.ref_name`，否则使用 `latest`）\n116:   - 登录到 GHCR (`GITHUB_TOKEN`)\n117:   - 设置 `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n118:   - 构建并推送多架构镜像:\n119:     - workloadmanager\n120:     - router\n121:     - picod\n122:   - 执行 `make docker-buildx-push-*`\n123: \n124: #### 11. 工作流审批工作流 (workflow-approval.yml)\n125: - **触发条件**: `pull_request_target` 到 `main` 或 `release-*` 分支（label/sync 事件）\n126: - **主要任务**:\n127:   - 检查贡献者是否为首次提交（PR 数量 ≤ 1）\n128:   - 检查 PR 是否有 `ok-to-test` 标签\n129:   - 如果不是首次贡献或有 `ok-to-test` 标签：\n130:     - 列出 head SHA 的 `action_required` 状态工作流运行\n131:     - 调用 `approveWorkflowRun` 批准每个工作流\n132: \n133: #### 12. 依赖更新工作流 (dependency-update.yml)\n134: - **触发条件**: 定时（每周一 UTC 0:00）或手动触发\n135: - **主要任务**:\n136:   - 更新 Go 依赖 (`go get -u ./...`, `go mod tidy`)\n137:   - 更新 Python 依赖 (`pip install --upgrade -r requirements.txt`)\n138:   - 运行测试验证更新\n139:   - 创建 Pull Request（如有变更）\n140:   - 自动标记 `dependencies` 标签\n141: \n142: ### Out of Scope\n143: \n144: - 性能测试和基准测试工作流（在单独的 AR 中处理）\n145: - 安全扫描工作流（如 Trivy、Snyk）（在单独的 AR 中处理）\n146: - 文档构建和部署工作流（在单独的 AR 中处理）\n147: - 跨云平台部署工作流（在单独的 AR 中处理）\n148: - 监控和告警工作流（在单独的 AR 中处理）\n149: - 本地开发环境设置（由 AR-033 Makefile 处理）\n150: \n151: ## Impact Analysis\n152: \n153: ### Components Impacted\n154: \n155: #### 1. GitHub Actions 工作流目录\n156: - 新增 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n157: - 创建 12 个 YAML 工作流文件\n158: - 创建共享 actions 和脚本（如需要）\n159: \n160: #### 2. Makefile 集成\n161: - 依赖 AR-033 的 Makefile 目标：\n162:   - `make docker-build`\n163:   - `make lint`\n164:   - `make gen-check`\n165:   - `make gen-copyright`\n166:   - `make e2e`\n167:   - `make e2e-clean`\n168:   - `make docker-buildx-push-*`\n169: \n170: #### 3. 容器镜像发布\n171: - 配置 GitHub Container Registry (GHCR)\n172: - 建立镜像命名规范\n173: - 支持多架构镜像构建 (amd64, arm64)\n174: \n175: #### 4. 代码质量标准\n176: - 强制执行 Go lint 规则\n177: - 强制执行 Python lint 规则\n178: - 强制执行代码生成一致性\n179: - 强制执行 Copyright 头部\n180: \n181: #### 5. Pull Request 流程\n182: - 自动运行 CI 检查\n183: - 要求所有检查通过才能合并\n184: - 首次贡献者需要工作流审批\n185: - 自动测试验证\n186: \n187: #### 6. 开发者工作流\n188: - 推送代码到 `main` 自动触发发布\n189: - 打 tag 自动触发版本发布\n190: - 依赖更新自动创建 PR\n191: \n192: ### Dependencies\n193: \n194: | 依赖 | 版本要求 | 用途 |\n195: |------|---------|------|\n196: | GitHub Actions | Latest | CI/CD 平台 |\n197: | Go | 1.24+ | Go 语言工具链 |\n198: | Python | 3.10+, 3.12 | Python 运行时 |\n199: | Docker | 20.10+ | 容器构建 |\n200: | Docker Buildx | Latest | 多架构构建 |\n201: | Kind | 0.30.0 | Kubernetes 本地集群 |\n202: | golangci-lint | 1.50+ | Go lint 工具 |\n203: | ruff | 0.1+ | Python lint 工具 |\n204: | pytest | 7.0+ | Python 测试框架 |\n205: | codespell | 2.2+ | 拼写检查 |\n206: | moreutils | Latest | sponge 命令 |\n207: | Make | 4.0+ | Make 执行引擎（依赖 AR-033） |\n208: \n209: ### Breaking Changes\n210: \n211: 无破坏性变更。这是新增功能，不影响现有工作流程。\n212: \n213: ### Performance Impact\n214: \n215: #### 1. CI/CD 执行时间\n216: - Pull Request: ~5-10 分钟（取决于触发的工作流）\n217: - Main 分支 Push: ~10-15 分钟（包括镜像构建和推送）\n218: - Tag 发布: ~15-20 分钟（多架构构建）\n219: \n220: #### 2. 资源消耗\n221: - GitHub Actions runner 使用:\n222:   - 标准工作流: 2-core, 7GB RAM\n223:   - E2E 测试: 4-core, 16GB RAM（需要 Kind）\n224:   - 多架构构建: 并行执行\n225: \n226: #### 3. 仓库大小\n227: - 工作流文件: ~50KB\n228: - 工件存储:\n229:   - Coverage 报告: ~1MB\n230:   - E2E 日志: ~50MB（仅失败时）\n231: - 无显著增长\n232: \n233: #### 4. 开发体验\n234: - Pull Request 检查时间: 稍长但更全面\n235: - 反馈速度: 快速（通常 5-10 分钟内）\n236: - 合并信心: 大幅提升（自动化验证）\n237: \n238: ## Design Decisions\n239: \n240: ### 工作流组织结构\n241: \n242: **选择**: 单独的工作流文件 + 共享逻辑\n243: \n244: **理由**:\n245: - 每个工作流独立运行，互不干扰\n246: - 便于路径过滤和条件触发\n247: - 易于维护和调试\n248: - 符合 GitHub Actions 最佳实践\n249: \n250: **目录结构**:\n251: ```\n252: .github/\n253: ├── workflows/\n254: │   ├── ci.yml                # CI 主工作流\n255: │   ├── lint.yml              # Go lint\n256: │   ├── codegen-check.yml     # 代码生成检查\n257: │   ├── test-coverage.yml     # 测试覆盖率\n258: │   ├── e2e.yml               # E2E 测试\n259: │   ├── python-sdk-test.yml   # Python SDK 测试\n260: │   ├── python-lint.yml       # Python lint\n261: │   ├── spelling.yml          # 拼写检查\n262: │   ├── copyright.yml         # Copyright 检查\n263: │   ├── release.yml           # 发布\n264: │   ├── workflow-approval.yml # 工作流审批\n265: │   └── dependency-update.yml # 依赖更新\n266: ├── actions/                  # 可选：共享 actions\n267: │   └── setup-go/\n268: └── scripts/                  # 可选：共享脚本\n269:     └── install-kind.sh\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 路径过滤策略\n273: \n274: **选择**: 使用 `paths` 过滤器减少不必要的工作流运行\n275: \n276: **理由**:\n277: - 节省 CI 资源和成本\n278: - 加速反馈循环\n279: - 只在相关代码变更时运行检查\n280: \n281: **实现**:\n282: ```yaml\n283: on:\n284:   pull_request:\n285:     paths:\n286:       - '**/*.go'\n287:       - 'go.mod'\n288:       - 'go.sum'\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 工作流并发控制\n292: \n293: **选择**: 使用 `concurrency` 组取消过时的运行\n294: \n295: **理由**:\n296: - 节省资源\n297: - 最新的代码获得优先处理\n298: - 避免队列堆积\n299: \n300: **实现**:\n301: ```yaml\n302: concurrency:\n303:   group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n304:   cancel-in-progress: true\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ### 缓存策略\n308: \n309: **选择**: 使用 GitHub Actions 缓存 Go modules、Python packages 和 Docker layers\n310: \n311: **理由**:\n312: - 显著加速工作流执行\n313: - 减少网络请求\n314: - 提高可靠性\n315: \n316: **实现**:\n317: ```yaml\n318: - uses: actions/cache@v4\n319:   with:\n320:     path: ~/go/pkg/mod\n321:     key: ${{ runner.os }}-go-${{ hashFiles('**/go.sum') }}\n322: ```\n323: \n324: ### 多架构镜像构建\n325: \n326: **选择**: 使用 Docker Buildx + QEMU\n327: \n328: **理由**:\n329: - 支持多平台 (amd64, arm64)\n330: - 单一工作流构建所有架构\n331: - 自动推送到 GHCR\n332: \n333: **实现**:\n334: ```yaml\n335: - uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n336: - uses: docker/setup-qemu-action@v3\n337: - run: make docker-buildx-push-workloadmanager IMAGE_TAG=${TAG}\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ### E2E 测试隔离\n341: \n342: **选择**: 使用 Kind 在隔离的 Kubernetes 集群中运行\n343: \n344: **理由**:\n345: - 接近生产环境\n346: - 完整的 Kubernetes 功能\n347: - 易于清理（`make e2e-clean`）\n348: - 不依赖外部资源\n349: \n350: **实现**:\n351: ```yaml\n352: - uses: helm/kind-action@v1\n353:   with:\n354:     version: v0.30.0\n355:     install_only: true\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ### 工作流审批机制\n359: \n360: **选择**: 对首次贡献者使用 `pull_request_target` + 手动审批\n361: \n362: **理由**:\n363: - 防止恶意代码执行\n364: - 保护仓库安全\n365: - 为已知贡献者提供自动审批\n366: \n367: **实现**:\n368: ```yaml\n369: on:\n370:   pull_request_target:\n371:     types: [labeled, synchronize]\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### 依赖更新策略\n375: \n376: **选择**: 定时 + 手动触发 + 自动 PR\n377: \n378: **理由**:\n379: - 定期更新避免过期\n380: - 便于测试验证\n381: - 保留人工审查\n382: \n383: **实现**:\n384: ```yaml\n385: on:\n386:   schedule:\n387:     - cron: '0 0 * * 1'  # 每周一 UTC 0:00\n388:   workflow_dispatch:\n389: ```\n390: \n391: ### 产物管理\n392: \n393: **选择**: 仅在失败时上传日志，覆盖率报告始终上传\n394: \n395: **理由**:\n396: - 节省存储空间\n397: - 便于调试失败\n398: - 保留测试覆盖率历史\n399: \n400: **实现**:\n401: ```yaml\n402: - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n403:   if: failure()\n404:   with:\n405:     name: e2e-logs\n406:     path: e2e-logs/\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### 通知机制\n410: \n411: **选择**: 使用 GitHub 内置通知（PR checks, status badges）\n412: \n413: **理由**:\n414: - 无需额外工具\n415: - 集成在 GitHub UI\n416: - 开发者熟悉\n417: \n418: **备选**: 后续可添加 Slack/Email 通知\n419: \n420: ## Alternatives Considered\n421: \n422: ### Alternative 1: 单一巨型工作流\n423: \n424: **描述**: 将所有 CI/CD 步骤合并到一个工作流文件中\n425: \n426: **优点**:\n427: - 文件数量少\n428: - 共享上下文简单\n429: - 易于查看完整流程\n430: \n431: **缺点**:\n432: - 单点故障，一个步骤失败影响所有\n433: - 无法并行执行\n434: - 路径过滤困难\n435: - 调试复杂\n436: - 资源利用率低\n437: \n438: **选择**: 不采纳 - 分离的工作流更灵活高效\n439: \n440: ### Alternative 2: 使用外部 CI/CD 工具\n441: \n442: **描述**: 使用 CircleCI、GitLab CI、Jenkins 等替代 GitHub Actions\n443: \n444: **优点**:\n445: - 可能提供更多功能\n446: - 独立于 GitHub\n447: - 可跨平台使用\n448: \n449: **缺点**:\n450: - 需要额外集成\n451: - 增加复杂性\n452: - 成本更高（通常）\n453: - 与 GitHub PR 流程集成不如 Actions 深度\n454: - 失去 GitHub Actions 生态系统优势\n455: \n456: **选择**: 不采纳 - GitHub Actions 与项目深度集成，成本效益最优\n457: \n458: ### Alternative 3: 使用复杂的工作流编排\n459: \n460: **描述**: 使用复杂的脚本和工具编排工作流（如 GitHub Action Toolkit）\n461: \n462: **优点**:\n463: - 更灵活的控制\n464: - 可复用逻辑\n465: \n466: **缺点**:\n467: - 增加维护成本\n468: - 调试困难\n469: - 学习曲线陡峭\n470: - 依赖外部脚本\n471: \n472: **选择**: 不采纳 - 简单的 YAML 工作流更易维护\n473: \n474: ### Alternative 4: 完全手动的 CI/CD\n475: \n476: **描述**: 不使用自动化，开发者在本地运行所有检查\n477: \n478: **优点**:\n479: - 零 CI 成本\n480: - 完全灵活\n481: \n482: **缺点**:\n483: - 一致性差\n484: - 容易遗漏\n485: - 不适合团队协作\n486: - 无法保护 `main` 分支\n487: - 无历史记录\n488: \n489: **选择**: 不采纳 - 自动化是现代开发实践的标准\n490: \n491: ### Alternative 5: 使用预提交钩子替代 CI\n492: \n493: **描述**: 仅使用 pre-commit hooks，不使用 CI/CD\n494: \n495: **优点**:\n496: - 本地快速反馈\n497: - 提交前拦截\n498: \n499: **缺点**:\n500: - 可以绕过（`--no-verify`）\n501: - 无法运行完整测试（如 E2E）\n502: - 无法保护 PR\n503: - 无法构建和推送镜像\n504: \n505: **选择**: 不采纳 - CI/CD 和 pre-commit 互补，都应有\n506: \n507: ### Alternative 6: 延迟工作流执行\n508: \n509: **描述**: 使用 GitHub Actions 的 `workflow_run` 事件延迟执行\n510: \n511: **优点**:\n512: - 可以先批准再运行\n513: - 减少资源浪费\n514: \n515: **缺点**:\n516: - 增加复杂度\n517: - 延迟反馈\n518: - 多个 PR 时容易混乱\n519: \n520: **选择**: 不采纳 - 即时反馈更重要\n521: \n522: ### Alternative 7: 仅在 PR 时运行，main 分支不运行\n523: \n524: **描述**: CI 只在 Pull Request 时运行，合并到 main 不运行\n525: \n526: **优点**:\n527: - 节省资源\n528: - 避免重复\n529: \n530: **缺点**:\n531: - 无法保护 main 分支\n532: - 无法自动发布镜像\n533: - 可能引入破坏性变更\n534: \n535: **选择**: 不采纳 - main 分支也需要保护（发布、测试）\n536: \n537: ## Implementation Plan\n538: \n539: ### Phase 1: 基础工作流 (Day 1-2)\n540: \n541: #### 1.1 创建目录结构\n542: - [ ] 创建 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n543: - [ ] 创建 `.github/actions/` 目录（如需要）\n544: - [ ] 创建 `.github/scripts/` 目录（如需要）\n545: \n546: #### 1.2 实现基础配置\n547: - [ ] 创建工作流模板\n548: - [ ] 设置并发控制\n549: - [ ] 配置缓存策略\n550: - [ ] 定义环境变量\n551: \n552: #### 1.3 实现 CI 工作流\n553: - [ ] 创建 `ci.yml`\n554: - [ ] 配置 Pull Request 触发\n555: - [ ] 设置 Docker Buildx\n556: - [ ] 执行 `make docker-build`\n557: - [ ] 测试和验证\n558: \n559: **检查清单**:\n560: - [ ] 目录结构创建\n561: - [ ] CI 工作流实现\n562: - [ ] Docker Buildx 配置\n563: - [ ] 并发控制\n564: - [ ] 缓存配置\n565: - [ ] 测试通过\n566: \n567: ### Phase 2: 代码质量工作流 (Day 2-3)\n568: \n569: #### 2.1 实现 Lint 工作流\n570: - [ ] 创建 `lint.yml`\n571: - [ ] 配置路径过滤\n572: - [ ] 设置 Go 1.24\n573: - [ ] 执行 `make lint`\n574: \n575: #### 2.2 实现 Python Lint 工作流\n576: - [ ] 创建 `python-lint.yml`\n577: - [ ] 配置路径过滤\n578: - [ ] 设置 Python 3.10\n579: - [ ] 执行 ruff 检查\n580: \n581: #### 2.3 实现 Codegen Check 工作流\n582: - [ ] 创建 `codegen-check.yml`\n583: - [ ] 配置路径过滤\n584: - [ ] 设置 Go 1.24.4\n585: - [ ] 执行 `make gen-check`\n586: \n587: #### 2.4 实现 Copyright 检查工作流\n588: - [ ] 创建 `copyright.yml`\n589: - [ ] 配置路径过滤\n590: - [ ] 安装 moreutils\n591: - [ ] 执行 `make gen-copyright`\n592: - [ ] 验证无变更\n593: \n594: **检查清单**:\n595: - [ ] Lint 工作流实现\n596: - [ ] Python Lint 工作流实现\n597: - [ ] Codegen Check 工作流实现\n598: - [ ] Copyright 检查工作流实现\n599: - [ ] 路径过滤验证\n600: - [ ] 测试通过\n601: \n602: ### Phase 3: 测试工作流 (Day 3-4)\n603: \n604: #### 3.1 实现测试覆盖率工作流\n605: - [ ] 创建 `test-coverage.yml`\n606: - [ ] 设置 Go 1.24\n607: - [ ] 运行竞态检测测试\n608: - [ ] 生成覆盖率报告\n609: - [ ] 上传 coverage.out 工件\n610: - [ ] 可选：配置 Codecov\n611: \n612: #### 3.2 实现 E2E 测试工作流\n613: - [ ] 创建 `e2e.yml`\n614: - [ ] 配置 Kind 安装\n615: - [ ] 设置 Go 1.23\n616: - [ ] 配置 ARTIFACTS_PATH\n617: - [ ] 执行 `make e2e`\n618: - [ ] 失败时上传日志\n619: - [ ] 执行 `make e2e-clean`\n620: \n621: #### 3.3 实现 Python SDK 测试工作流\n622: - [ ] 创建 `python-sdk-test.yml`\n623: - [ ] 配置路径过滤\n624: - [ ] 设置 Python 3.12\n625: - [ ] 切换到 `sdk-python/`\n626: - [ ] 安装 pytest 和 SDK\n627: - [ ] 运行测试\n628: \n629: **检查清单**:\n630: - [ ] 测试覆盖率工作流实现\n631: - [ ] E2E 测试工作流实现\n632: - [ ] Python SDK 测试工作流实现\n633: - [ ] Kind 配置\n634: - [ ] 工件上传\n635: - [ ] 清理逻辑\n636: - [ ] 测试通过\n637: \n638: ### Phase 4: 质量保证工作流 (Day 4)\n639: \n640: #### 4.1 实现拼写检查工作流\n641: - [ ] 创建 `spelling.yml`\n642: - [ ] 安装 codespell\n643: - [ ] 配置文件备份/恢复逻辑\n644: - [ ] 执行 codespell 检查\n645: - [ ] 配置忽略列表\n646: \n647: **检查清单**:\n648: - [ ] 拼写检查工作流实现\n649: - [ ] 文件备份/恢复逻辑\n650: - [ ] codespell 配置\n651: - [ ] 测试通过\n652: \n653: ### Phase 5: 发布工作流 (Day 4-5)\n654: \n655: #### 5.1 实现发布工作流\n656: - [ ] 创建 `release.yml`\n657: - [ ] 配置 push 触发（main 和 tags）\n658: - [ ] 确定 TAG 逻辑\n659: - [ ] 配置 GHCR 登录\n660: - [ ] 构建并推送多架构镜像\n661:   - workloadmanager\n662:   - router\n663:   - picod\n664: \n665: #### 5.2 配置镜像命名\n666: - [ ] 定义镜像命名规范\n667: - [ ] 配置 IMAGE_REGISTRY\n668: - [ ] 测试镜像推送\n669: \n670: **检查清单**:\n671: - [ ] 发布工作流实现\n672: - [ ] TAG 逻辑\n673: - [ ] GHCR 配置\n674: - [ ] 多架构构建\n675: - [ ] 镜像命名\n676: - [ ] 测试通过\n677: \n678: ### Phase 6: 安全和治理工作流 (Day 5)\n679: \n680: #### 6.1 实现工作流审批工作流\n681: - [ ] 创建 `workflow-approval.yml`\n682: - [ ] 配置 `pull_request_target` 触发\n683: - [ ] 实现首次贡献者检测\n684: - [ ] 检查 `ok-to-test` 标签\n685: - [ ] 自动审批逻辑\n686: - [ ] 调用 GitHub API\n687: \n688: #### 6.2 实现依赖更新工作流\n689: - [ ] 创建 `dependency-update.yml`\n690: - [ ] 配置定时触发（每周一）\n691: - [ ] 配置手动触发\n692: - [ ] 更新 Go 依赖\n693: - [ ] 更新 Python 依赖\n694: - [ ] 运行测试验证\n695: - [ ] 创建 Pull Request\n696: - [ ] 添加 `dependencies` 标签\n697: \n698: **检查清单**:\n699: - [ ] 工作流审批实现\n700: - [ ] 首次贡献者检测\n701: - [ ] API 调用\n702: - [ ] 依赖更新实现\n703: - [ ] 定时触发\n704: - [ ] 自动 PR\n705: - [ ] 测试通过\n706: \n707: ### Phase 7: 集成和测试 (Day 5-6)\n708: \n709: #### 7.1 集成所有工作流\n710: - [ ] 验证工作流独立运行\n711: - [ ] 验证工作流协同工作\n712: - [ ] 测试路径过滤\n713: - [ ] 测试并发控制\n714: \n715: #### 7.2 端到端测试\n716: - [ ] 创建测试 PR\n717: - [ ] 验证所有检查运行\n718: - [ ] 验证失败情况\n719: - [ ] 验证成功情况\n720: - [ ] 测试合并到 main\n721: - [ ] 测试 tag 发布\n722: \n723: #### 7.3 性能优化\n724: - [ ] 优化缓存策略\n725: - [ ] 优化并行执行\n726: - [ ] 减少不必要的工作流运行\n727: - [ ] 监控执行时间\n728: \n729: **检查清单**:\n730: - [ ] 所有工作流集成\n731: - [ ] 端到端测试\n732: - [ ] 路径过滤验证\n733: - [ ] 性能优化\n734: - [ ] 文档更新\n735: \n736: ### Phase 8: 文档和培训 (Day 6)\n737: \n738: #### 8.1 编写文档\n739: - [ ] 更新 README.md\n740: - [ ] 创建 CI/CD 指南\n741: - [ ] 创建故障排查指南\n742: - [ ] 创建贡献者指南\n743: \n744: #### 8.2 配置状态徽章\n745: - [ ] 添加 CI 徽章\n746: - [ ] 添加测试覆盖率徽章\n747: - [ ] 添加发布徽章\n748: \n749: #### 8.3 团队培训\n750: - [ ] 记录 CI/CD 流程\n751: - [ ] 准备最佳实践\n752: - [ ] 准备常见问题\n753: \n754: **检查清单**:\n755: - [ ] 文档完成\n756: - [ ] 徽章配置\n757: - [ ] 指南完成\n758: - [ ] 团队培训材料\n759: \n760: ## Testing Strategy\n761: \n762: ### Unit Tests\n763: \n764: #### 工作流语法测试\n765: - 验证 YAML 语法正确性\n766: - 测试所有工作流可以加载\n767: - 验证 actions 引用正确\n768: \n769: #### 脚本测试\n770: - 测试自定义脚本（如 install-kind.sh）\n771: - 验证脚本退出码\n772: - 测试错误处理\n773: \n774: ### Integration Tests\n775: \n776: #### Pull Request 测试\n777: 1. **完整流程测试**\n778:    - 创建测试 PR\n779:    - 验证所有相关工作流触发\n780:    - 验证所有检查通过\n781:    - 合并 PR\n782: \n783: 2. **路径过滤测试**\n784:    - 修改 Go 文件：验证 lint、codegen-check、test-coverage 运行\n785:    - 修改 Python 文件：验证 python-lint、python-sdk-test 运行\n786:    - 修改文档：验证拼写检查运行\n787:    - 修改无关文件：验证无工作流运行\n788: \n789: 3. **失败场景测试**\n790:    - 引入 Lint 错误：验证工作流失败\n791:    - 引入测试失败：验证工作流失败\n792:    - 引入代码生成漂移：验证工作流失败\n793:    - 验证失败 PR 无法合并\n794: \n795: #### 发布测试\n796: 1. **Main 分支发布测试**\n797:    - 推送到 main\n798:    - 验证 release 工作流触发\n799:    - 验证镜像构建和推送\n800:    - 验证镜像标签为 `latest`\n801: \n802: 2. **Tag 发布测试**\n803:    - 创建测试 tag (v0.0.1-test)\n804:    - 验证 release 工作流触发\n805:    - 验证镜像构建和推送\n806:    - 验证镜像标签为 `v0.0.1-test`\n807: \n808: 3. **多架构测试**\n809:    - 验证 amd64 镜像构建\n810:    - 验证 arm64 镜像构建\n811:    - 验证 manifest 创建\n812: \n813: #### E2E 测试\n814: 1. **正常流程测试**\n815:    - 验证 Kind 集群创建\n816:    - 验证 `make e2e` 成功\n817:    - 验证清理逻辑执行\n818: \n819: 2. **失败场景测试**\n820:    - 故意破坏 E2E 测试\n821:    - 验证日志上传\n822:    - 验证清理逻辑仍执行\n823: \n824: ### Regression Tests\n825: \n826: #### 向后兼容性\n827: - 验证现有 Makefile 目标仍可用\n828: - 验证本地开发流程不受影响\n829: - 验证现有 PR 流程兼容\n830: \n831: #### 破坏性变更检测\n832: - 监控工作流行为变化\n833: - 验证检查结果一致性\n834: - 验证镜像构建产物一致\n835: \n836: ### Performance Tests\n837: \n838: #### 执行时间测试\n839: - 测量各工作流执行时间\n840: - 测量完整 PR 检查时间\n841: - 测量发布流程时间\n842: - 对比优化前后性能\n843: \n844: #### 资源使用测试\n845: - 监控 Actions runner 使用\n846: - 监控磁盘空间使用\n847: - 监控网络请求次数\n848: \n849: ### Security Tests\n850: \n851: #### 权限测试\n852: - 验证 `pull_request_target` 权限正确\n853: - 验证 GHCR 访问权限\n854: - 验证 GitHub API 权限\n855: \n856: #### 注入测试\n857: - 验证工作流无法被恶意 PR 滥用\n858: - 验证首次贡献者无法直接执行工作流\n859: - 验证敏感信息不泄露\n860: \n861: ## API Specification\n862: \n863: ### 工作流触发器\n864: \n865: ```yaml\n866: # Pull Request 触发\n867: on:\n868:   pull_request:\n869:     branches: [main, release-*]\n870:     paths: ['**/*.go']\n871: \n872: # Push 触发\n873: on:\n874:   push:\n875:     branches: [main]\n876:     tags: ['v*.*.*']\n877: \n878: # 定时触发\n879: on:\n880:   schedule:\n881:     - cron: '0 0 * * 1'\n882: \n883: # 手动触发\n884: on:\n885:   workflow_dispatch:\n886: ```\n887: \n888: ### 环境变量\n889: \n890: ```yaml\n891: env:\n892:   GO_VERSION: '1.24'\n893:   PYTHON_VERSION: '3.12'\n894:   DOCKER_REGISTRY: 'ghcr.io'\n895:   IMAGE_NAME: 'agentcube'\n896: ```\n897: \n898: ### 工件上传\n899: \n900: ```yaml\n901: - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n902:   with:\n903:     name: coverage-report\n904:     path: coverage.out\n905:     retention-days: 30\n906: \n907: - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n908:   if: failure()\n909:   with:\n910:     name: e2e-logs\n911:     path: e2e-logs/\n912: ```\n913: \n914: ### 缓存配置\n915: \n916: ```yaml\n917: - uses: actions/cache@v4\n918:   with:\n919:     path: ~/go/pkg/mod\n920:     key: ${{ runner.os }}-go-${{ hashFiles('**/go.sum') }}\n921:     restore-keys: |\n922:       ${{ runner.os }}-go-\n923: \n924: - uses: actions/cache@v4\n925:   with:\n926:     path: ~/.cache/pip\n927:     key: ${{ runner.os }}-pip-${{ hashFiles('**/requirements.txt') }}\n928: ```\n929: \n930: ### 并发控制\n931: \n932: ```yaml\n933: concurrency:\n934:   group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n935:   cancel-in-progress: true\n936: ```\n937: \n938: ### 路径过滤\n939: \n940: ```yaml\n941: on:\n942:   pull_request:\n943:     paths:\n944:       - '**/*.go'\n945:       - 'go.mod'\n946:       - 'go.sum'\n947:       - '.golangci.yml'\n948: ```\n949: \n950: ### 条件执行\n951: \n952: ```yaml\n953: - name: Run if PR from first-time contributor\n954:   if: github.event.pull_request.author_association == 'FIRST_TIME_CONTRIBUTOR'\n955:   run: echo \"First-time contributor\"\n956: \n957: - name: Upload on failure\n958:   if: failure()\n959:   uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n960: \n961: - name: Always run\n962:   if: always()\n963:   run: make e2e-clean\n964: ```\n965: \n966: ### Matrix 策略\n967: \n968: ```yaml\n969: strategy:\n970:   matrix:\n971:     os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest]\n972:     go: ['1.23', '1.24']\n973: ```\n974: \n975: ## Configuration\n976: \n977: ### 必需配置\n978: \n979: #### GitHub Secrets\n980: | Secret | 用途 | 说明 |\n981: |--------|------|------|\n982: | `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR 认证 | 自动提供，无需配置 |\n983: \n984: #### GitHub Settings\n985: | 设置 | 值 | 说明 |\n986: |------|-----|------|\n987: | Actions permissions | Enable | 启用 GitHub Actions |\n988: | Workflow permissions | Read and write permissions | 允许工作流写入仓库 |\n989: | Branch protection rules | Require status checks | 要求所有检查通过才能合并 |\n990: \n991: ### 可选配置\n992: \n993: #### 环境变量\n994: | 变量 | 默认值 | 说明 |\n995: |------|--------|------|\n996: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | Go 版本 |\n997: | `PYTHON_VERSION` | `3.12` | Python 版本 |\n998: | `KIND_VERSION` | `v0.30.0` | Kind 版本 |\n999: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `ghcr.io` | 镜像仓库 |\n1000: \n1001: #### Codecov（可选）\n1002: | Secret | 用途 |\n1003: |--------|------|\n1004: | `CODECOV_TOKEN` | Codecov 上传 |\n1005: \n1006: ### 仓库设置\n1007: \n1008: #### Branch Protection\n1009: ```yaml\n1010: required_status_checks:\n1011:   strict: true\n1012:   contexts:\n1013:     - CI\n1014:     - Lint\n1015:     - Test Coverage\n1016:     - Python SDK Tests\n1017:     - Python Lint\n1018:     - Spelling Check\n1019:     - Copyright Check\n1020:     - Codegen Check\n1021: ```\n1022: \n1023: #### Labels\n1024: - `ok-to-test`: 允许首次贡献者测试\n1025: - `dependencies`: 依赖更新 PR\n1026: - `skip-ci`: 跳过 CI（谨慎使用）\n1027: \n1028: ## Security Considerations\n1029: \n1030: ### 工作流安全\n1031: \n1032: #### 1. Pull Request 目标安全\n1033: - 使用 `pull_request_target` 处理需要更高权限的工作流\n1034: - 验证贡献者身份\n1035: - 首次贡献者需要审批\n1036: \n1037: #### 2. Secret 管理\n1038: - 不在工作流中硬编码密钥\n1039: - 使用 GitHub Secrets 存储敏感信息\n1040: - 限制 Secret 访问范围\n1041: \n1042: #### 3. 第三方 Actions\n1043: - 使用固定版本（如 `@v4`）\n1044: - 定期更新 Actions\n1045: - 审查 Actions 源代码\n1046: \n1047: #### 4. 代码注入防护\n1048: - 不使用 `eval` 或类似危险操作\n1049: - 验证所有输入\n1050: - 使用沙箱环境运行用户代码\n1051: \n1052: ### 镜像安全\n1053: \n1054: #### 1. 基础镜像\n1055: - 使用官方或可信镜像\n1056: - 定期更新基础镜像\n1057: - 扫描漏洞\n1058: \n1059: #### 2. 镜像内容\n1060: - 不在镜像中包含密钥\n1061: - 使用多阶段构建最小化攻击面\n1062: - 非 root 用户运行\n1063: \n1064: #### 3. 镜像签名（可选）\n1065: - 考虑使用 Cosign 签名镜像\n1066: - 验证镜像签名\n1067: \n1068: ### 依赖安全\n1069: \n1070: #### 1. Go 依赖\n1071: - 使用 `go.sum` 固定版本\n1072: - 定期运行 `go mod tidy`\n1073: - 使用 `go mod verify` 验证\n1074: \n1075: #### 2. Python 依赖\n1076: - 固定依赖版本\n1077: - 定期更新和测试\n1078: - 使用虚拟环境\n1079: \n1080: #### 3. 工具依赖\n1081: - 固定工具版本\n1082: - 从可信源下载\n1083: - 验证哈希\n1084: \n1085: ### 访问控制\n1086: \n1087: #### 1. GHCR 访问\n1088: - 使用 `GITHUB_TOKEN` 自动认证\n1089: - 限制镜像可见性（private/public）\n1090: - 定期审计访问日志\n1091: \n1092: #### 2. GitHub API\n1093: - 使用最小必要权限\n1094: - 限制 API 调用频率\n1095: - 记录 API 使用\n1096: \n1097: ## Performance Considerations\n1098: \n1099: ### 执行时间优化\n1100: \n1101: #### 1. 缓存策略\n1102: - Go modules 缓存\n1103: - Python packages 缓存\n1104: - Docker layers 缓存\n1105: - 缓存命中率目标: 80%+\n1106: \n1107: #### 2. 并行执行\n1108: - 独立工作流并行运行\n1109: - Matrix 策略并行测试\n1110: - 避免串行依赖\n1111: \n1112: #### 3. 增量执行\n1113: - 路径过滤减少不必要的工作流\n1114: - 跳过未变更的检查\n1115: - 只构建变更的组件\n1116: \n1117: ### 资源优化\n1118: \n1119: #### 1. Runner 使用\n1120: - 使用标准 runner（2-core, 7GB RAM）\n1121: - E2E 测试使用 larger runner（如需要）\n1122: - 避免资源浪费\n1123: \n1124: #### 2. 存储优化\n1125: - 限制工件保留时间\n1126: - 仅在失败时上传日志\n1127: - 定期清理旧工件\n1128: \n1129: #### 3. 网络优化\n1130: - 使用缓存减少下载\n1131: - 并行下载依赖\n1132: - 使用最近的镜像源\n1133: \n1134: ### 成本控制\n1135: \n1136: #### 1. 工作流限制\n1137: - 限制并发工作流数量\n1138: - 设置执行超时\n1139: - 取消过时的运行\n1140: \n1141: #### 2. 监控和告警\n1142: - 监控 Actions 分钟数\n1143: - 设置成本告警\n1144: - 定期审查成本\n1145: \n1146: ## Monitoring and Metrics\n1147: \n1148: ### 关键指标\n1149: \n1150: #### 执行指标\n1151: - 工作流成功率\n1152: - 平均执行时间\n1153: - 失败率（按工作流分类）\n1154: - 缓存命中率\n1155: \n1156: #### 质量指标\n1157: - 测试覆盖率\n1158: - Lint 错误数\n1159: - 代码生成漂移数\n1160: - Copyright 不一致数\n1161: \n1162: #### 开发者体验\n1163: - PR 检查时间\n1164: - 反馈延迟\n1165: - 合并延迟\n1166: - 开发者满意度\n1167: \n1168: ### 日志记录\n1169: \n1170: #### 工作流日志\n1171: - 所有工作流输出到 GitHub Actions 日志\n1172: - 保留时间: 90 天（GitHub 默认）\n1173: - 关键步骤添加时间戳\n1174: \n1175: #### 失败日志\n1176: - 失败时上传详细日志\n1177: - 包含环境信息\n1178: - 便于调试\n1179: \n1180: #### 工件\n1181: - Coverage 报告\n1182: - E2E 日志（失败时）\n1183: - 测试结果\n1184: - 构建产物（如需要）\n1185: \n1186: ### 告警\n1187: \n1188: #### 失败告警\n1189: - 关键工作流失败时通知\n1190: - 使用 GitHub notifications\n1191: - 可选：集成 Slack/Discord\n1192: \n1193: #### 性能告警\n1194: - 执行时间异常增加\n1195: - 失败率增加\n1196: - 成本超预算\n1197: \n1198: ### 仪表板\n1199: \n1200: #### GitHub 提供的\n1201: - Actions 标签页\n1202: - 工作流运行历史\n1203: - 检查状态\n1204: \n1205: #### 可选：自定义\n1206: - Grafana 仪表板\n1207: - 定制化指标\n1208: - 跨项目对比\n1209: \n1210: ## Success Criteria\n1211: \n1212: - 所有 12 个工作流正常工作\n1213: - Pull Request 检查准确且完整\n1214: - 所有检查通过率 > 95%\n1215: - 测试覆盖率 > 80%\n1216: - 平均 PR 检查时间 < 10 分钟\n1217: - E2E 测试稳定运行\n1218: - 镜像发布成功率 100%\n1219: - 无安全漏洞\n1220: - 文档完整准确\n1221: - 开发者满意度高\n1222: - CI/CD 成本可控\n1223: \n1224: ## Open Questions\n1225: \n1226: 1. **Q1**: 是否需要集成安全扫描工作流（如 Trivy、Snyk）？\n1227:    - **当前**: 不包含在 AR-034 中\n1228:    - **讨论**: 安全扫描是重要的 CI/CD 组件\n1229:    - **决策**: 在单独的 AR 中处理（如 AR-035）\n1230: \n1231: 2. **Q2**: 是否需要配置 Codecov？\n1232:    - **当前**: 可选配置\n1233:    - **讨论**: Codecov 提供更好的覆盖率可视化\n1234:    - **决策**: 初始不配置，后续根据需求添加\n1235: \n1236: 3. **Q3**: 是否需要支持其他容器仓库（如 Docker Hub）？\n1237:    - **当前**: 仅支持 GHCR\n1238:    - **讨论**: 多仓库增加复杂性\n1239:    - **决策**: 初始仅 GHCR，后续根据需求扩展\n1240: \n1241: 4. **Q4**: E2E 测试是否需要使用 larger runner？\n1242:    - **当前**: 使用标准 runner\n1243:    - **讨论**: E2E 测试可能需要更多资源\n1244:    - **决策**: 初始使用标准 runner，性能不足时升级\n1245: \n1246: 5. **Q5**: 是否需要配置 Slack/Email 通知？\n1247:    - **当前**: 仅使用 GitHub 内置通知\n1248:    - **讨论**: 外部通知提高可见性\n1249:    - **决策**: 初始不配置，后续根据团队需求添加\n1250: \n1251: 6. **Q6**: 是否需要支持手动触发所有工作流？\n1252:    - **当前**: 仅 dependency-update 支持手动触发\n1253:    - **讨论**: 便于调试和重试\n1254:    - **决策**: 关键工作流添加手动触发\n1255: \n1256: ## Next Steps\n1257: \n1258: 1. 实现 Phase 1-2（基础和代码质量工作流）\n1259: 2. 实现 Phase 3（测试工作流）\n1260: 3. 实现 Phase 4（拼写检查）\n1261: 4. 实现 Phase 5（发布工作流）\n1262: 5. 实现 Phase 6（安全和治理）\n1263: 6. 实现 Phase 7（集成和测试）\n1264: 7. 实现 Phase 8（文档和培训）\n1265: 8. 监控和优化\n1266: 9. 收集用户反馈\n1267: 10. 持续改进\n1268: \n1269: ## References\n1270: \n1271: - [GitHub Actions Documentation](https://docs.github.com/en/actions)\n1272: - [GitHub Actions Best Practices](https://docs.github.com/en/actions/learn-github-actions/best-practices-for-github-actions)\n1273: - [Docker Buildx](https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/)\n1274: - [Kind Documentation](https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/)\n1275: - [golangci-lint](https://golangci-lint.run/)\n1276: - [Ruff](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff)\n1277: - [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/)\n1278: - [Codecov](https://about.codecov.io/)\n1279: - [GitHub Container Registry](https://docs.github.com/en/packages/working-with-a-github-packages-registry/working-with-the-container-registry)\n1280: - [AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系](../AR-033/proposal.md)\n1281: - [AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建](../AR-032/proposal.md)\n1282: - [CI/CD Specification](../../ci-cd/spec.md)\n1283: - [AgentCube Project](../../README.md)\n\n(End of file - total 1283 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\n为 AgentCube 项目实现 12 个 GitHub Actions 工作流，提供完整的 CI/CD 自动化能力。这些工作流将覆盖构建、测试、代码质量检查、端到端测试、Python SDK 验证、镜像发布等关键流程，确保代码质量和持续交付的可靠性。\n\n## Purpose\n\n实现完整的 CI/CD 自动化体系，达到以下目标：\n\n- **自动化验证** - 对 Pull Request 自动执行构建、Lint、测试、代码生成漂移检查\n- **质量保证** - 多层次的代码质量检查（Go Lint、Python Lint、Spelling、Copyright）\n- **测试覆盖** - 单元测试、集成测试、端到端测试、覆盖率报告\n- **持续交付** - 自动构建和推送多架构容器镜像到 GHCR\n- **开发体验** - 简化开发流程，快速反馈代码问题\n- **多语言支持** - 同时支持 Go 和 Python 项目的工作流\n- **Kubernetes 集成** - 在 Kind 上运行 E2E 测试\n- **安全合规** - 工作流审批机制保护首次贡献者\n\n## Module","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775885395878,"end":1775885395895}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775885395927,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04a7ba0010j13jhp9VGDj65","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b04951b0012SKFi65HAVv63q","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":46174,"input":292,"output":251,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":45631}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775885409440,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b04dc9f0012d8FGvHc0UPpht","messageID":"msg_d7b04a7f20014occwrQZRxqlQH","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885653593,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b089541001k2Mnaoh5NIJ1p0","messageID":"msg_d7b04a7f20014occwrQZRxqlQH","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b3982b42ebc44c3e9c2fbb5e3de68ddd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-034\n- **Title**: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n- **Module**: .github\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for 12 GitHub Actions workflows providing comprehensive CI/CD automation for the AgentCube project. The workflows cover build verification, linting, testing, code quality checks, end-to-end testing, Python SDK validation, container image publishing, dependency updates, and workflow approval mechanisms to ensure code quality and reliable continuous delivery.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CI workflow build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches using Docker Buildx.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build verification on pull request\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the CI workflow job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL checkout the repository\n- **AND** Docker Buildx SHALL be set up with default builder instance\n- **AND** `docker` and `buildx` versions SHALL be verified and logged\n- **AND** `make docker-build` SHALL be executed successfully\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL report success if build completes\n\n#### Scenario: CI workflow triggers on correct branches\n- **GIVEN** the CI workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** a pull request is created\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL trigger only for `main` branch\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL trigger only for branches matching `release-*` pattern\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL NOT trigger for other branches\n\n#### Scenario: CI workflow uses appropriate runner\n- **GIVEN** the CI workflow job configuration\n- **WHEN** the workflow runs\n- **THEN** the job SHALL use `ubuntu-latest` runner\n- **AND** the job SHALL have access to Docker\n\n#### Scenario: CI workflow failure handling\n- **GIVEN** the CI workflow with build step\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build` fails\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail the job\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL report the failure in PR checks\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL provide error logs for debugging\n\n### Requirement: Go lint workflow with path filtering\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to Go files\n- **WHEN** path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n- **THEN** the Lint workflow SHALL run\n- **AND** Go version 1.24 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** `make lint` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** lint results SHALL be reported\n\n#### Scenario: Lint workflow skips on non-Go changes\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with only documentation changes\n- **WHEN** path filter does not match Go-related paths\n- **THEN** the Lint workflow SHALL skip execution\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL report success without running lint\n\n#### Scenario: Lint workflow reports Go lint errors\n- **GIVEN** the Lint workflow with golangci-lint execution\n- **WHEN** golangci-lint detects lint errors\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n- **AND** the PR SHALL show failing check status\n\n#### Scenario: Lint workflow passes on clean code\n- **GIVEN** the Lint workflow with clean Go code\n- **WHEN** golangci-lint completes without errors\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL succeed\n- **AND** the PR SHALL show passing check status\n- **AND** lint summary SHALL be displayed\n\n### Requirement: Code generation check workflow\nThe system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change on pull requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen check on API changes\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to `pkg/apis/**` directory\n- **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** Go version 1.24.4 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** `make gen-check` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL verify no git diff exists after regeneration\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL fail if drift is detected\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen check on Makefile changes\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** `make gen-check` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** generated artifacts SHALL be regenerated\n- **AND** git diff SHALL be checked for changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL verify consistency\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen check on workflow changes\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to `.github/workflows/**`\n- **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** `make gen-check` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** workflow-generated artifacts SHALL be verified\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL ensure no drift\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen check failure on drift\n- **GIVEN** the Codegen Check workflow with detected drift\n- **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` returns non-zero exit code\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** drift SHALL be reported to the user\n- **AND** instructions SHALL be provided to run `make gen-all`\n\n### Requirement: Test coverage workflow with race detection\nThe system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, uploading coverage reports as artifacts.\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage test execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request or merge group triggering coverage path filter\n- **WHEN** the Test Coverage workflow runs\n- **THEN** Go version 1.24 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** free disk space SHALL be freed if needed\n- **AND** `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** `coverage.out` SHALL be uploaded as artifact\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage path filtering\n- **GIVEN** the Test Coverage workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding media/docs)\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run for most code changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL skip for `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` files\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for `**` pattern with exclusions\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage artifact upload\n- **GIVEN** the Test Coverage workflow with completed tests\n- **WHEN** coverage.out is generated\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL upload `coverage.out` as artifact\n- **AND** artifact SHALL be retained for 30 days\n- **AND** artifact SHALL be downloadable for review\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage with Codecov integration\n- **GIVEN** the Test Coverage workflow with Codecov token secret\n- **WHEN** coverage tests complete successfully\n- **THEN** Codecov upload action SHALL be executed\n- **AND** coverage report SHALL be uploaded to Codecov\n- **AND** coverage percentage SHALL be displayed in PR comments\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage test failure handling\n- **GIVEN** the Test Coverage workflow with failing tests\n- **WHEN** `go test` returns non-zero exit code\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** test failures SHALL be reported with details\n- **AND** coverage.out SHALL still be uploaded if generated\n\n### Requirement: E2E testing workflow on Kind\nThe system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure and ensuring cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: E2E test execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n- **THEN** `ARTIFACTS_PATH` SHALL be set to `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n- **AND** Kind tool v0.30.0 SHALL be installed with `install_only: true`\n- **AND** Go version 1.23 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** `make e2e` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** E2E tests SHALL run in Kind cluster\n\n#### Scenario: E2E test log capture on failure\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow with failing tests\n- **WHEN** `make e2e` fails\n- **THEN** `e2e-logs` directory SHALL be uploaded as artifact\n- **AND** artifact SHALL contain component logs and describes\n- **AND** logs SHALL be available for debugging\n\n#### Scenario: E2E test cleanup always runs\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow regardless of test outcome\n- **WHEN** tests complete (success or failure)\n- **THEN** `make e2e-clean` SHALL be executed in `always` condition\n- **AND** Kind cluster SHALL be deleted\n- **AND** temporary artifacts SHALL be cleaned up\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Kind cluster configuration\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow Kind setup\n- **WHEN** Kind is installed via `helm/kind-action@v1`\n- **THEN** version SHALL be v0.30.0\n- **AND** `install_only: true` SHALL prevent double cluster creation\n- **AND** cluster creation SHALL be handled by `run_e2e.sh`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E workflow uses appropriate runner\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow job configuration\n- **WHEN** the workflow runs\n- **THEN** the job SHALL use Ubuntu runner\n- **AND** the runner SHALL support Kind execution\n- **AND** sufficient resources SHALL be available for cluster\n\n### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests workflow\nThe system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes on pull requests and merge groups.\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK test execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to `sdk-python/**` directory\n- **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow runs\n- **THEN** Python version 3.12 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** working directory SHALL be `sdk-python/`\n- **AND** `pip install pytest` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** `pip install -e .` SHALL install SDK in editable mode\n- **AND** `python -m pytest tests/ -v` SHALL be executed\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK path filtering\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** path filter `sdk` matches `sdk-python/**`\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run for SDK changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL skip for non-SDK changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL use paths-filter action\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK test failure reporting\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow with failing tests\n- **WHEN** pytest detects test failures\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** test failures SHALL be reported with verbose output\n- **AND** failing tests SHALL be identified by name and traceback\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK test passes\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow with all tests passing\n- **WHEN** pytest completes successfully\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL succeed\n- **AND** test summary SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** PR check SHALL show passing status\n\n### Requirement: Python lint workflow\nThe system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n\n#### Scenario: Python lint execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes to Python files\n- **WHEN** path filter matches Python-related paths\n- **THEN** Python version 3.10 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** `pip install ruff` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** lint SHALL check entire repository from root\n\n#### Scenario: Python lint path filtering\n- **GIVEN** the Python Lint workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** path filter `python` matches specified paths\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run for `cmd/cli/**` changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for `sdk-python/**` changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for `example/**` changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for `test/**/*.py` changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for `pyproject.toml` changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL run for workflow file changes\n\n#### Scenario: Python lint uses project configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Python Lint workflow execution\n- **WHEN** ruff is invoked\n- **THEN** `--config pyproject.toml` SHALL be passed\n- **AND** project-specific lint rules SHALL be applied\n- **AND** configuration SHALL be respected\n\n#### Scenario: Python lint error reporting\n- **GIVEN** the Python Lint workflow with lint errors\n- **WHEN** ruff detects lint issues\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** lint errors SHALL be reported with file and line numbers\n- **AND** error codes SHALL be displayed\n\n### Requirement: Spelling check workflow with file exclusion\nThe system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell execution with file backup\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n- **THEN** `pip install codespell` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` SHALL be backed up or moved at repo root\n- **AND** nested copies SHALL be found and moved via `find`\n- **AND** codespell SHALL run with `--check-filenames`\n- **AND** skipped globs SHALL be applied\n- **AND** ignored words list `fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` SHALL be applied\n- **AND** backed-up files SHALL be restored\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Codespell workflow execution\n- **WHEN** codespell is invoked\n- **THEN** `--check-filenames` flag SHALL be used\n- **AND** `--skip` globs SHALL exclude specified patterns\n- **AND** `--ignore-words-list` SHALL include `fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn`\n- **AND** check SHALL run on `.` (current directory)\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell finds spelling errors\n- **GIVEN** the Codespell workflow with spelling errors\n- **WHEN** codespell detects misspelled words\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** spelling errors SHALL be reported with file and line\n- **AND** suggested corrections SHALL be displayed\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell passes on clean text\n- **GIVEN** the Codespell workflow with no spelling errors\n- **WHEN** codespell completes without issues\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL succeed\n- **AND** PR check SHALL show passing status\n- **AND** file restore SHALL complete successfully\n\n### Requirement: Copyright header check workflow\nThe system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright check execution\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with changes triggering copyright path filter\n- **WHEN** the Copyright Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** `apt install moreutils` SHALL install sponge command\n- **AND** `make gen-copyright` SHALL be executed\n- **AND** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL verify no changes\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL succeed if no diff\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright path filtering\n- **GIVEN** the Copyright Check workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** path filter `copyright` matches\n- **THEN** the filter SHALL include all files except `*.md`\n- **AND** the filter SHALL exclude `*.svg` files\n- **AND** the filter SHALL exclude `*.png` files\n- **AND** the filter SHALL exclude `docs/**` directory\n- **AND** the filter SHALL exclude `.github/**` directory\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright check detects missing headers\n- **GIVEN** the Copyright Check workflow with files missing copyright\n- **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` adds headers\n- **THEN** `git diff` SHALL show changes\n- **AND** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL fail\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL fail\n- **AND** files needing headers SHALL be identified\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright check passes with proper headers\n- **GIVEN** the Copyright Check workflow with all files having headers\n- **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` completes\n- **THEN** `git diff` SHALL be empty\n- **AND** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL succeed\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL succeed\n\n### Requirement: Release image publication workflow\nThe system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n\n#### Scenario: Tag selection for image tags\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow on `push` event\n- **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`\n- **THEN** `TAG` environment variable SHALL be set to `github.ref_name`\n- **AND** image SHALL be tagged with version from tag\n- **AND** workflow SHALL use semantic version as tag\n\n#### Scenario: Latest tag for main branch pushes\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow on `push` to `main` branch\n- **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is not `tag`\n- **THEN** `TAG` environment variable SHALL be set to `latest`\n- **AND** image SHALL be tagged as `latest`\n- **AND** workflow SHALL push latest image\n\n#### Scenario: GHCR login and push\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow with built images\n- **WHEN** images are ready to push\n- **THEN** `docker/login-action` SHALL login to `ghcr.io`\n- **AND** `GITHUB_TOKEN` SHALL be used for authentication\n- **AND** login SHALL succeed with proper permissions\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-architecture image build and push\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow with Docker Buildx set up\n- **WHEN** building and pushing images\n- **THEN** `IMAGE_REGISTRY` SHALL be set to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n- **AND** `make docker-buildx-push` SHALL build and push workloadmanager\n- **AND** `make docker-buildx-push-router` SHALL build and push router\n- **AND** `make docker-buildx-push-picod` SHALL build and push picod\n- **AND** each image SHALL support multiple architectures (amd64, arm64)\n- **AND** `*_IMAGE` variables SHALL include `:${TAG}` suffix\n\n#### Scenario: Release workflow triggers\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** push occurs to `main` branch\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL trigger\n- **AND** it SHALL build and push `latest` tagged images\n- **AND** push to `main` SHALL NOT trigger tag-based release\n\n#### Scenario: Semantic version tag triggers\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** push creates tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL trigger\n- **AND** it SHALL build and push version-tagged images\n- **AND** tag SHALL be used as image tag\n\n#### Scenario: Release workflow uses Go 1.24.4\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow job configuration\n- **WHEN** the workflow runs\n- **THEN** Go version 1.24.4 SHALL be set up\n- **AND** build SHALL use specified Go version\n- **AND** Go version SHALL match other workflows\n\n### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\nThe system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n\n#### Scenario: Approve action_required for repeat contributors\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-**`\n- **WHEN** contributor has more than one PR\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for head SHA\n- **AND** it SHALL filter for `action_required` status\n- **AND** it SHALL call `approveWorkflowRun` for each run\n- **AND** workflows SHALL be approved automatically\n\n#### Scenario: Approve with ok-to-test label\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` with `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** labeled or synchronize events occur\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL check for `ok-to-test` label\n- **AND** if label exists, workflows SHALL be approved\n- **AND** first-time contributors can use label to bypass wait\n\n#### Scenario: Skip approval for first-time contributors\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` from first-time contributor\n- **WHEN** contributor has only one PR and no `ok-to-test` label\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL NOT approve workflows\n- **AND** workflows SHALL remain in `action_required` state\n- **AND** manual approval SHALL be required\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow approval triggers\n- **GIVEN** the Workflow Approval workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** `pull_request_target` events occur\n- **THEN** `labeled` event type SHALL trigger workflow\n- **AND** `synchronize` event type SHALL trigger workflow\n- **AND** target branches SHALL be `main` or `release-**`\n\n#### Scenario: GitHub API usage for approval\n- **GIVEN** the Workflow Approval workflow execution\n- **WHEN** approving workflow runs\n- **THEN** `github-script` action SHALL be used\n- **AND** it SHALL query GitHub API for workflow runs\n- **AND** it SHALL filter by head SHA and status\n- **AND** it SHALL call approval API for each run\n\n### Requirement: Dependency update workflow\nThe system SHALL periodically update Go and Python dependencies and create pull requests for review.\n\n#### Scenario: Scheduled dependency update\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** scheduled time arrives (Monday UTC 0:00)\n- **THEN** `go get -u ./...` SHALL update Go dependencies\n- **AND** `go mod tidy` SHALL clean up go.mod and go.sum\n- **AND** `pip install --upgrade -r requirements.txt` SHALL update Python dependencies\n- **AND** tests SHALL be run to verify updates\n- **AND** Pull Request SHALL be created if changes exist\n\n#### Scenario: Manual dependency update trigger\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow configuration\n- **WHEN** `workflow_dispatch` event is triggered manually\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run dependency updates\n- **AND** it SHALL follow same steps as scheduled run\n- **AND** it SHALL allow on-demand updates\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency update creates PR\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow with dependency changes\n- **WHEN** updates are verified and tests pass\n- **THEN** a Pull Request SHALL be created\n- **AND** PR SHALL include all dependency changes\n- **AND** PR SHALL have `dependencies` label\n- **AND** PR description SHALL summarize updates\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency update verification\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow after updates\n- **WHEN** dependencies are updated\n- **THEN** tests SHALL be executed to verify compatibility\n- **AND** test failures SHALL prevent PR creation\n- **AND** workflow SHALL fail if tests don't pass\n\n#### Scenario: No updates scenario\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow execution\n- **WHEN** no dependency updates are available\n- **THEN** workflow SHALL complete successfully\n- **AND** no Pull Request SHALL be created\n- **AND** workflow SHALL report no changes\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency update branch management\n- **GIVEN** the Dependency Update workflow creating PR\n- **WHEN** preparing changes\n- **THEN** a new branch SHALL be created\n- **AND** branch name SHALL follow naming convention\n- **AND** changes SHALL be committed to branch\n- **AND** branch SHALL be pushed to remote\n\n### Requirement: Workflow concurrency control\nThe system SHALL use concurrency groups to cancel in-progress workflow runs when newer commits are pushed.\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrency group per workflow and ref\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with concurrency configured\n- **WHEN** multiple commits are pushed quickly\n- **THEN** concurrency group SHALL be `${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}`\n- **AND** in-progress runs SHALL be cancelled\n- **AND** only latest run SHALL complete\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrency cancellation behavior\n- **GIVEN** an in-progress workflow run\n- **WHEN** a new commit triggers the same workflow\n- **THEN** older run SHALL be cancelled\n- **AND** newer run SHALL proceed\n- **AND** resources SHALL be freed from cancelled run\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrency for different branches\n- **GIVEN** workflow runs on different branches\n- **WHEN** runs occur concurrently\n- **THEN** runs SHALL NOT cancel each other\n- **AND** each branch SHALL have separate concurrency group\n- **AND** runs SHALL complete independently\n\n### Requirement: Workflow caching strategy\nThe system SHALL use GitHub Actions cache to speed up workflow execution by caching Go modules, Python packages, and Docker layers.\n\n#### Scenario: Go modules caching\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with Go dependency setup\n- **WHEN** cache action is configured\n- **THEN** cache path SHALL be `~/go/pkg/mod`\n- **THEN** cache key SHALL be `${{ runner.os }}-go-${{ hashFiles('**/go.sum') }}`\n- **AND** restore keys SHALL include `${{ runner.os }}-go-`\n- **AND** cache SHALL speed up dependency downloads\n\n#### Scenario: Python packages caching\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with Python dependency setup\n- **WHEN** cache action is configured\n- **THEN** cache path SHALL be `~/.cache/pip`\n- **AND** cache key SHALL be `${{ runner.os }}-pip-${{ hashFiles('**/requirements.txt') }}`\n- **AND** cache SHALL speed up pip installs\n\n#### Scenario: Docker layer caching\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with Docker Buildx\n- **WHEN** build cache is configured\n- **THEN** Docker layer cache SHALL be utilized\n- **AND** cache SHALL be stored in GitHub Actions cache\n- **AND** cache SHALL speed up image builds\n\n#### Scenario: Cache miss scenario\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with cache configuration\n- **WHEN** cache key does not match any existing cache\n- **THEN** cache SHALL be a miss\n- **AND** dependencies SHALL be downloaded normally\n- **AND** new cache SHALL be created after download\n\n### Requirement: Workflow artifact management\nThe system SHALL manage artifacts appropriately, uploading logs on failure and coverage reports always.\n\n#### Scenario: Upload coverage report artifact\n- **GIVEN** the Test Coverage workflow\n- **WHEN** `coverage.out` is generated\n- **THEN** artifact SHALL be uploaded with name `coverage-report` or `go-coverage`\n- **AND** artifact SHALL be retained for 30 days\n- **AND** artifact SHALL be downloadable\n\n#### Scenario: Upload E2E logs on failure\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow with test failures\n- **WHEN** `if: failure()` condition is met\n- **THEN** `e2e-logs` directory SHALL be uploaded\n- **AND** artifact SHALL contain component logs\n- **AND** artifact SHALL contain pod describes\n- **AND** artifact retention period SHALL be appropriate\n\n#### Scenario: No artifact upload on success\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow with passing tests\n- **WHEN** tests complete successfully\n- **THEN** `e2e-logs` artifact SHALL NOT be uploaded\n- **AND** disk space SHALL be saved\n- **AND** workflow SHALL complete without artifact\n\n#### Scenario: Artifact naming and retention\n- **GIVEN** workflow artifact uploads\n- **WHEN** artifacts are uploaded\n- **THEN** artifact names SHALL be descriptive\n- **AND** retention days SHALL be configured appropriately\n- **AND** artifacts SHALL be accessible from workflow run page\n\n### Requirement: Workflow status reporting\nThe system SHALL provide clear status reporting for pull requests and workflow runs.\n\n#### Scenario: PR check status display\n- **GIVEN** a pull request with workflow runs\n- **WHEN** workflows complete\n- **THEN** each workflow SHALL display check status in PR\n- **AND** status SHALL be passing, failing, or pending\n- **AND** status SHALL link to workflow run details\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow run summary\n- **GIVEN** a completed workflow run\n- **WHEN** viewing the run summary\n- **THEN** job steps SHALL be listed\n- **AND** each step SHALL show success or failure\n- **AND** logs SHALL be available for each step\n\n#### Scenario: Failure notification\n- **GIVEN** a failing workflow\n- **WHEN** workflow fails\n- **THEN** failure SHALL be reported in PR checks\n- **AND** failing workflow SHALL be highlighted\n- **AND** error details SHALL be available\n\n#### Scenario: Success notification\n- **GIVEN** a successful workflow\n- **WHEN** workflow completes successfully\n- **THEN** success SHALL be reported in PR checks\n- **AND** green checkmark SHALL be displayed\n- **AND** workflow SHALL not block PR merge\n\n### Requirement: Workflow permissions and security\nThe system SHALL use appropriate permissions and security measures for GitHub Actions workflows.\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow read permissions\n- **GIVEN** a workflow with default permissions\n- **WHEN** workflow needs to read repository content\n- **THEN** `contents: read` permission SHALL be sufficient\n- **AND** workflow SHALL be able to checkout code\n- **AND** workflow SHALL not have write access unless needed\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow write permissions for release\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow\n- **WHEN** workflow needs to push images\n- **THEN** `contents: write` permission SHALL be required\n- **AND** `GITHUB_TOKEN` SHALL have registry write permissions\n- **AND** workflow SHALL be able to authenticate with GHCR\n\n#### Scenario: Pull request target security\n- **GIVEN** the Workflow Approval workflow using `pull_request_target`\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** workflow SHALL run with repository permissions\n- **THEN** workflow SHALL NOT run with PR author permissions\n- **AND** security SHALL be maintained against malicious PRs\n\n#### Scenario: Secret handling\n- **GIVEN** workflows using secrets\n- **WHEN** secrets are referenced\n- **THEN** secrets SHALL be stored in GitHub Secrets\n- **THEN** secrets SHALL NOT be hardcoded in workflows\n- **AND** secret values SHALL be masked in logs\n\n### Requirement: Workflow timeout and resource limits\nThe system SHALL configure appropriate timeouts and resource limits for workflow execution.\n\n#### Scenario: Job timeout configuration\n- **GIVEN** workflow job configuration\n- **WHEN** job is defined\n- **THEN** timeout-minutes SHALL be set appropriately\n- **AND** default timeout SHALL be reasonable (e.g., 30 minutes)\n- **AND** long-running jobs SHALL have extended timeouts\n\n#### Scenario: E2E workflow timeout\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow job\n- **WHEN** job runs\n- **THEN** timeout-minutes SHALL account for cluster setup\n- **AND** timeout-minutes SHALL account for test execution\n- **AND** timeout-minutes SHALL account for cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build timeout\n- **GIVEN** the Release workflow with Docker builds\n- **WHEN** building multi-architecture images\n- **THEN** timeout SHALL be sufficient for multiple architectures\n- **AND** timeout SHALL account for network transfer\n- **AND** timeout SHALL prevent indefinite hangs\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout failure behavior\n- **GIVEN** a workflow job exceeding timeout\n- **WHEN** timeout is reached\n- **THEN** job SHALL be terminated\n- **AND** workflow SHALL report timeout failure\n- **AND** logs SHALL show timeout message\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ CI workflow builds Docker image on PR to main/release-* branches\n2. ✅ Lint workflow runs golangci-lint with Go path filtering\n3. ✅ Codegen check workflow verifies no drift on API/Makefile changes\n4. ✅ Test coverage workflow runs race-enabled tests with coverage report\n5. ✅ E2E workflow runs tests in Kind with log capture on failure\n6. ✅ Python SDK tests run pytest on sdk-python changes\n7. ✅ Python lint runs Ruff with Python path filtering\n8. ✅ Spelling check runs codespell with file exclusions\n9. ✅ Copyright check verifies headers with path filtering\n10. ✅ Release workflow builds and pushes multi-architecture images to GHCR\n11. ✅ Workflow approval approves runs for repeat contributors or ok-to-test label\n12. ✅ Dependency update workflow periodically updates Go and Python dependencies\n13. ✅ Workflow concurrency cancels in-progress runs appropriately\n14. ✅ Workflow caching speeds up Go modules, Python packages, and Docker layers\n15. ✅ Workflow artifacts manage logs and reports appropriately\n16. ✅ Workflow status reporting provides clear PR check feedback\n17. ✅ Workflow permissions use appropriate security measures\n18. ✅ Workflow timeouts prevent indefinite runs\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- GitHub Actions (Latest)\n- Go 1.24+ (for most workflows), Go 1.24.4 (for codegen check), Go 1.23 (for E2E)\n- Python 3.10+ (for Python lint), Python 3.12 (for Python SDK tests)\n- Docker 20.10+ with Buildx\n- Kind v0.30.0 (for E2E testing)\n- golangci-lint 1.50+ (for Go lint)\n- Ruff 0.1+ (for Python lint)\n- pytest 7.0+ (for Python testing)\n- codespell 2.2+ (for spelling check)\n- moreutils (sponge command) (for copyright check)\n- Base Design: `ci-cd/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 (for Make target integration)\n- AR: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (for Docker build integration)\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines new GitHub Actions workflows that provide CI/CD automation for the AgentCube project. The workflows are additive and do not change existing build processes, output formats, or runtime behavior. They provide automated verification and quality checks without breaking any existing functionality, workflows, or deployments. Existing development and release processes can continue to work alongside the new CI/CD workflows.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Pull Request Target Security**: The Workflow Approval workflow uses `pull_request_target` to run with repository permissions, preventing malicious PRs from abusing elevated privileges.\n2. **Secret Management**: All secrets are stored in GitHub Secrets and referenced securely, never hardcoded in workflow files.\n3. **Third-Party Actions**: All third-party GitHub Actions use pinned versions (e.g., `@v4`) and are regularly reviewed and updated.\n4. **GHCR Authentication**: Container registry uses `GITHUB_TOKEN` for automatic authentication with appropriate permissions.\n5. **First-Time Contributor Protection**: Workflow approval mechanism prevents untrusted contributors from running workflows with elevated permissions.\n6. **Code Injection Prevention**: Workflows avoid dangerous operations like `eval` and validate all inputs.\n7. **Dependency Verification**: Go and Python dependency updates include test verification before creating PRs.\n8. **Artifact Security**: Artifacts are managed with appropriate retention periods and do not contain sensitive information.\n9. **Minimal Permissions**: Workflows use the minimum required permissions (read vs write) based on their needs.\n10. **Base Image Security**: Docker builds use official or trusted base images with multi-stage builds to minimize attack surface.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Workflow Syntax Tests\n- Validate all 12 workflow YAML files have correct syntax\n- Test all workflows can be loaded by GitHub Actions\n- Verify all action references are correct and use pinned versions\n- Test workflow triggers and event filters\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Create test PRs to verify workflow triggers\n- Test path filtering for each workflow\n- Verify workflow execution on different branch patterns\n- Test workflow failure scenarios and error reporting\n- Verify PR check status reporting\n- Test workflow concurrency and cancellation\n- Test artifact upload and download\n\n### Release Workflow Tests\n- Test main branch push triggers `latest` image build\n- Test semantic version tag triggers versioned image build\n- Verify multi-architecture image builds (amd64, arm64)\n- Test GHCR authentication and push\n- Verify image tagging and naming\n\n### E2E Workflow Tests\n- Test Kind cluster creation and cleanup\n- Verify E2E test execution in cluster\n- Test log capture on failure\n- Verify cleanup logic always runs\n- Test artifact upload on failure\n\n### Lint and Quality Workflow Tests\n- Introduce lint errors and verify workflow failure\n- Test code generation drift detection\n- Verify copyright header checking\n- Test spelling check with false positive handling\n- Verify Python lint with Ruff configuration\n\n### Security Tests\n- Verify `pull_request_target` permissions\n- Test first-time contributor approval logic\n- Verify secret handling and masking\n- Test workflow access restrictions\n\n### Performance Tests\n- Measure workflow execution times\n- Test caching effectiveness\n- Verify concurrency cancellation\n- Monitor resource usage\n\n### End-to-End Tests\n- Complete PR lifecycle: create, checks pass, merge\n- Verify release workflow triggers on main merge\n- Test tag creation and release workflow\n- Verify dependency update PR creation\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `ci-cd/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n- AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n- AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n- GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n- GitHub Actions Best Practices: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/learn-github-actions/best-practices-for-github-actions\n- Docker Buildx Documentation: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n- Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n- GitHub Container Registry: https://docs.github.com/en/packages/working-with-a-github-packages-registry/working-with-the-container-registry","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885653564,"end":1775885653589}}}}
