{"type":"text","timestamp":1775885667748,"sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","part":{"id":"prt_d7b08c0aa001wf8PWEZx0SMTlL","messageID":"msg_d7b08968a0010Vq4nY7mOE2wYu","sessionID":"ses_284fbd590ffelBZUAcAfEZ4Bda","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written the delta-spec.md file for AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows). The specification includes:\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **18 major requirements** covering all 12 workflows plus cross-cutting concerns\n- **80+ GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios** providing detailed acceptance criteria\n- **All 12 workflows specified**: CI, Lint, Codegen Check, Test Coverage, E2E, Python SDK Tests, Python Lint, Spelling Check, Copyright Check, Release, Workflow Approval, and Dependency Update\n\n**Workflow Coverage:**\n- Build verification with Docker Buildx\n- Go and Python linting with path filtering\n- Code generation drift detection\n- Race-enabled test coverage\n- E2E testing on Kind with log capture\n- Multi-architecture image publishing to GHCR\n- First-time contributor approval mechanism\n- Automated dependency updates\n\n**Additional Requirements:**\n- Concurrency control for workflow cancellation\n- Caching strategy (Go modules, Python packages, Docker layers)\n- Artifact management (logs on failure, coverage always)\n- Status reporting for PR checks\n- Security (permissions, secrets, pull_request_target)\n- Timeout and resource limits\n\nThe specification follows the OpenSpec format with comprehensive acceptance criteria and is ready for implementation.","time":{"start":1775885667746,"end":1775885667746}}}
